4:
I suppose this means... Business is
concluded?
6:
That would be nice, wouldn't it? But
there's still the matter of cleanup.
14:
The infamous dark mage of the
Kaleidoscope! I'd heard the rumors,
but to actually meet you... It's an
honor.
17:
Was there something you wanted
from us? I am, of course, especially
open to business inquiries!
21:
Hmm... Perhaps I'll indulge you just
this once.
30:
Well now. It's no wonder I didn't
notice a thing, despite the mess he
made of my domain...
34:
I'll handle the disposal of this, as well
as mopping up the rest of his mess.
37:
A word of warning before I go—this
isn't the last you've seen of the
dragons.
41:
Heh. If you want to preserve your
world, then you'd better be ready to
do what's necessary...
46:
Hold it! What exactly are you up to
here?
51:
Perhaps my words were wasted on
you after all.
Like I said—leave the rest to me.
58:
A-anyway, we're done here now,
right?
61: If we are, then it's time to go home.
70:
It was an honor to see the might of
the esteemed Swallow Knights in
action!
72:
Please. There is only a single knight
now, as you can see.
75:
I wouldn't be here at all if it weren't
for my comrades. Besides, I had a
lot of help from the gallant knights
of the Farlands.
78:
I am sorry I failed to aid you in the
incident three years ago.
81:
Weren't you negotiating with
Palpebra at the time?
84:
Thanks to your political endeavors,
we now have this treaty of
friendship. Your priorities were in the
right place.
86:
If that's truly how you feel... It would
lift a burden off my shoulders.
87:
I must say, however... You don't look
like you've aged a day in the past
three years.
89:
That would be because I was frozen
in time.
93:
I couldn't recover the relic. I have
failed you, Ciel.
97:
Raise your head, Cel. You have, in
fact, exceeded my expectations.
99:
The Sweses will have their hands full,
there is no doubt about that. But you
have shown the world the might of
the Tris.
103:
With all due respect, in my failure I
have failed to display any might
whatsoever!
107:
I was mostly joking. The people of
Palpebra are reasonable, and
seeing us uphold our end of the
treaty was an important step in
solidifying it.
110:
In other words, the average citizen
will care more that a soldier of Tris
did all she could to protect lives
instead of reclaiming a relic.
112:
Still, I wonder if it was the right move
to reveal our most powerful knight...
Or should that title be reserved for
our father?
117:
Since when did you become such a
schemer?
If we're done here, then I'm going
home!
121:
I am to be a politician from now on.
That also means I don't have much
use for Enlil anymore. Would you do
me the honor of accepting it into
your care?
126: ...Very well. I shall wield it with pride.
129:
There is one more thing: the Oxtan
man at the heart of today's incident.
He'll be brought to us, correct?
132:
Um... He should be. At least... if he's
still alive by then...
140:
Does the name Velgar Solon ring
any bells? Or how about the
assassination of a member of the
royal family 30 years ago? And don't
lie—you're going to tell me
everything you know.
145:
Hey! You promised you wouldn't be
mean!
150:
I'm not being "mean", I'm just asking
him questions!
153:
I know what you're speaking of. I'll
tell you all I can.
166:
Why did you wander off by yourself?
How many times have I told you not
to do that!
174:
Is that the latest fad? Saying
"whatever" to everything? Stop
giving me that attitude right now!
183: Arum, is there a reason you left?
193:
How come when it's Stella asking,
you answer so nicely?
198:
Now, now, Arly. She'll see this as a
victory if you lose your temper.
207:
Alk always makes me cookies, so I
wanted to make some for him too!
211:
I had to find a shop with cookie stuff
in it!
214:
Just because you bought
ingredients doesn't mean you can
actually bake.
224:
We all start somewhere, don't we?
With a few lessons, I'm sure—
229:
Lessons? Do you even know how to
bake? Because I sure don't.
233:
N-neither do I! But we know
someone who does...
243:
Huh? What? Please tell me it's not
more dragons.
248:
So you want to give someone a
present... but you need them to help
you actually make it. How does that
make sense?
252:
Doesn't it depend on the person and
the task? In Alk's case, I think he'd be
more than happy to assist.
258:
Um... Can you teach me how to
make cookies?
267:
I'd LOVE to teach you! Oh, what kind
of cookies should we make? Do you
wanna start right now?
